OL,3,CDeaf boy, 10, wants to help others
OL,4,Cafter therapy helped him communicate
OL,6,FCurrently, fewer than 10% of deaf
OL,7,Fchildren can access the therapy
OL,8,Fdespite 84% of adults believing it
OL,9,Fshould be available through the NHS.
OL,11,FHowever, in Wales there are no
OL,12,Fqualified auditory verbal therapists.
OL,14,FIn order to receive the therapy,
OL,15,FNathaniel's mother Siobhan recounted
OL,16,Fhow they had to travel from Wales to
OL,17,FOxford every two weeks for three years
OL,18,Ffor hour-long appointments.
