OL,3,CDeaf boy, 10, wants to help others
OL,4,Cafter therapy helped him communicate
OL,6,F"But things need to change for other
OL,7,FWelsh families with deaf children now.
OL,8,FAwareness, ambition and investment are
OL,9,Fall so low and this is just not fair."
OL,11,FHarrison explained how the therapy
OL,12,Fallowed him to pursue his love of
OL,13,Fmusic, saying: "It is thanks to the
OL,14,Fdetermination of my parents to get
OL,15,Fearly and effective support for me
OL,16,Fwith auditory verbal therapy that I
OL,17,Fdon't feel being deaf has held me back
OL,18,Fin any way. I love music, can play
OL,19,Fguitar, and saxophone and have a huge
OL,20,Fpassion for sport especially surfing."
